social_posts.post_text: So…..I can’t believe my baby @calilynndreamtaylor is growing up into such a beautiful young lady..last night she went to @the_combs_twins futuristic fashion themed 16th birthday party and had a blast 🥳🥳

On this #mlkday I am humbled and grateful that my book  #thelittlegirlwholosthersmile has touched so many.

Because of Dr.King, (the person I most admire) a young black school teacher was able to author and publish her own book that helps children who are challenged with the effects of divorce and separation.

Thank you @anaismirabelle and your beautiful mother for including my book as part of your literacy project.

For more information on my book, you can visit my other page @ilovetiffney and click the link in the bio. or send me a direct message. 

Happy King Day!

I sat for a long time pondering if I should post this. Usually what we see on IG is picture perfect.. honestly we all present what we consider to be our best selves. But what about times like these where  our wounds and scars light the way for others. 
My mother died of breast cancer.
My grandmother died of breast cancer.
My aunts have died from cancer.
I’m 47.
I’ve been #BRACAtested…

I noticed another lump in my breast.
A large mass that felt like an uncomfortable knot. I did not wait or hesitate. Neither should you. I immediately went and got checked. Come to find out it was a cyst that needed to be surgically removed and tested.
Imagine…knowing my past… how I felt. 😔
How worried and concerned I was..
My thought process as a mother…
BUT GOD.
I got my results back..
CANCER FREE!!!!!

THANK YOU GOD. THANK YOU JESUS!! …
who is the Author and Finisher of my Faith.

Ladies PLEASE STAY ON TOP OF YOUR BREAST HEALTH!!! 💕💕💕💕💕💕💕

King Justice,
From the very first time I looked at you, I knew you would always be my whole heart. My first words to you were, “I love you Justice..it’s me and you forever”…and for the past 16 years I’ve told you I love you every single day, and I mean it. 

You’re my back bone, my strength, my peace, and my calm. You take  care of your mama. You’re  everything a son should be.
You’re more than my child, you’re my friend.
My first born, my son.. I adore you.

Happy 16th Birthday Justice.. it is, and always will be - me & you forever. 🫶🏽
